# 1) All nitrogens are treated only as proton donors. Their acceptor
# valencies are consistently set to 0.
# 
# 2) For His, the charges on ND1 and NE2 could be +1 or 0 (depending
# on the pH). But I indicated these atoms as having a single + charge to
# account for an optimistic hydrogen bonding scenario.
# 
# 3) In all cases where there is a charge resonance (eg. OD1/OD2 of ASP), I
# have given both atoms a unit charge.
#
# 4) various amides NH seem to be an acceptor too (according to statistics,
#    partly because they may be mislabeled in structures, ie N, Q sidechains)
#
#                                Donor Acceptor 
#                                  Valencies      Charge
#
ATMGRP 'N'
  ATOM            '*'       'N'       1       1       0
ATMGRP  'O'
  ATOM            '*'       'O'       0       2       0
ATMGRP  'SG'
  ATOM            'CYS'     'SG'      1       0       0
ATMGRP  'OD1/2'
  ATOM            'ASP'     'OD1'     0       2       -0.5
  ATOM            'ASP'     'OD2'     0       2       -0.5
ATMGRP  'OE1/2'
  ATOM            'GLU'     'OE1'     0       2       -0.5
  ATOM            'GLU'     'OE2'     0       2       -0.5
ATMGRP  'ND1'
  ATOM            'HSD'     'ND1'     1       0        0
ATMGRP  'NE2'
  ATOM            'HSD'     'NE2'     1       0        0
ATMGRP  'NZ'
  ATOM            'LYS'     'NZ'      3       0       +1
ATMGRP  'SD'
  ATOM            'MET'     'SD'      0       0       0
ATMGRP  'OD1'
  ATOM            'ASN'     'OD1'     0       2       0
ATMGRP  'ND2'
  ATOM            'ASN'     'ND2'     2       1       0
ATMGRP  'OE1'
  ATOM            'GLN'     'OE1'     0       2       0
ATMGRP  'NE2'
  ATOM            'GLN'     'NE2'     2       1       0
ATMGRP  'NE'
  ATOM            'ARG'     'NE'      1       0       0
ATMGRP  'NH1/2'
  ATOM            'ARG'     'NH1'     2       0       +0.5
  ATOM            'ARG'     'NH2'     2       0       +0.5
ATMGRP  'OG'
  ATOM            'SER'     'OG'      1       2       0
ATMGRP  'OG1'
  ATOM            'THR'     'OG1'     1       2       0
ATMGRP  'NE1'
  ATOM            'TRP'     'NE1'     1       0       0
ATMGRP  'OH'
  ATOM            'TYR'     'OH'      1       0       0
ATMGRP  'SG2'
  ATOM            'CSS'     'SG'      0       0       0
ATMGRP  'NH3'
  ATOM            '*'       'NH3'     2       0       +1
ATMGRP  'OT1/2'
  ATOM            '*'       'OT1'     0       2       -0.5
  ATOM            '*'       'OT2'     0       2       -0.5
ATMGRP  '*:*'
  ATOM            '*'       '*'       0       0       0
  ATOM            '*'       '*'       0       0       0
